data.content:
p: AGNI, thy faithful servant I call upon thee with many a gift, As in the keeping of the great inciting God;
p: Thou who ne’er movest thee to aid the indolent, the godless man, Him who though wealthy never brings an offering.
p: Splendid, O Singer, is that man, mightiest of the great in heaven. Agni, may we be foremost, we thy worshippers.
